{cite news|title=Telegraphic News |date= 24 May 1899 |newspaper=The Northern Miner |location=Charters Towers, Queensland, Australia |page=3 |access-date=28 April 2020 |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article84868256 |via=Trove}}</ref> and was still editor in February 1903, when he sprained his ankle as the result of a fall and was hospitalised in [[Townsville]]. He died there a week later.\n\n[[Frank Fox (author)|Frank Fox]] (born 10 August 1874), author and editor of ''[[The Lone Hand (magazine)|The Lone Hand]]'' (and much else) was a son.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Fox, Charles James}}\n[[Category:1827 births]]\n[[Category:1903 deaths]]\n[[Category:Australian newspaper editors]]\n[[Category:Australian Roman Catholics]]\n", "name_user": "Wbm1058", "label": "safe", "comment": "miscapitalization", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_James_Fox_(editor)"}
